An applicant for a permit as an apprentice diabetes educator shall:
File a written application on forms provided by the board in order to practice and earn the experience required for a type of license application;
Engage in the practice of diabetes education while receiving qualifying experience with a board-approved supervisor who shall assume responsibility for and supervise the apprentice diabetes educatorâ€™s practice;
Not practice diabetes education until a supervisor has been approved by the board;
Cease the practice of diabetes education immediately upon the supervisorâ€™s inability or unwillingness to act as the supervisor; and
Upon gaining the required supervision hours and completing a board-approved diabetes educator course, apply for licensure as a licensed diabetes educator.
